{
  "texts": [
    "The BIC score is widely popular and has been",
    "found to be able to learn the true network faster than other scoring functions such as AIC, BDeu and fNML (Liu et al. 2012).",
    "While both the AIC and BIC scores can recover the underlying network when the sample size is sufficiently high, they are suboptimal with limited sample sizes.",
    "To that end, Silander et al. (2010) proposed the factorized Normalized Maximum Likelihood (fNML) score.",
    "fNML is based on the Normalised Maximum Likelihood (NML) distribution which gives the probability of every possible dataset of sample size N for a specific graph G."
  ]
}